1
00:00:00,080 --> 00:00:04,293
If your survey includes open-text answers, QualCanvas can bring them

2
00:00:04,293 --> 00:00:08,084
into the same visual coding workflow as interview material.

3
00:00:08,084 --> 00:00:12,297
Start with a clean CSV exported from your survey system,

4
00:00:12,297 --> 00:00:16,088
and remove fields you do not need for analysis.

5
00:00:16,488 --> 00:00:21,056
Inside a canvas, choose Survey to open the CSV importer.

6
00:00:21,056 --> 00:00:25,624
Select the file only after checking its first row contains

7
00:00:25,624 --> 00:00:30,192
clear column headings and each response occupies a consistent row.

8
00:00:30,592 --> 00:00:34,940
After the file is read, map the column that names

9
00:00:34,940 --> 00:00:39,288
each item, the column containing the open-text response and, when

10
00:00:39,288 --> 00:00:41,028
appropriate, a case field.

11
00:00:41,028 --> 00:00:45,376
Use a research identifier rather than a participant's real name.

12
00:00:45,776 --> 00:00:49,020
Open Sources and spot-check several imported items.

13
00:00:49,020 --> 00:00:53,655
Confirm the response count, make sure headings have not become

14
00:00:53,655 --> 00:00:58,289
content and check that line breaks and characters survived the

15
00:00:58,289 --> 00:00:59,216
CSV export.

16
00:00:59,616 --> 00:01:05,798
Code meaningful excerpts rather than treating every row as a single idea.

17
00:01:05,798 --> 00:01:10,950
The source, selected passage, code and later analytical structure remain

18
00:01:10,950 --> 00:01:15,072
connected, which makes survey interpretations easier to review.

19
00:01:15,472 --> 00:01:20,198
A CSV can quietly contain email addresses, IP fields or

20
00:01:20,198 --> 00:01:22,561
demographic combinations that identify someone.

21
00:01:22,561 --> 00:01:27,287
Remove unnecessary columns, follow your consent and retention rules, and

22
00:01:27,287 --> 00:01:32,014
use the Ethics panel as a project reminder rather than

23
00:01:32,014 --> 00:01:33,904
a substitute for approval.

24
00:01:34,304 --> 00:01:38,906
The reliable path is simple: prepare a minimal CSV, map

25
00:01:38,906 --> 00:01:43,509
the columns, verify the imported sources and then code visibly.

26
00:01:43,509 --> 00:01:48,111
Open the QualCanvas training centre for the next tutorial on

27
00:01:48,111 --> 00:01:49,952
cases and cross-case comparison.
